# SESSION PROTOCOL

## ON SESSION START (MANDATORY)

**STOP. Execute before any work:**

```bash
python3 scripts/status.py
```

Then state: "Phase: ___. Current version: ___. Last action: ___. Next step: ___."

If unclear -> ASK USER. If clear -> proceed.

---

## CONTEXT UPDATE TRIGGERS

| When | Update What |
|------|-------------|
| After finding papers | `refs.db` via `scripts/refs.py add` |
| After reading a paper | `refs.db` via `scripts/refs.py update --append-notes` |
| After validating an idea | `idea_versions/`, `validations/`, `refs.db` links, sketch.md |
| After evaluating a direction | `directions/`, sketch.md |
| After direction decision | `decisions.md`, sketch.md |
| After insight/pattern found | `findings.md` |
| Before risky pivot | `git commit` + sketch.md |
| At session end | sketch.md (full state) + `git add doc/agent/ refs.db && git commit` |

**Heuristic: If session crashes now, would the next session know what happened?**

