# PAPER DISCOVERY & READING

**IMPORTANT: These methods apply to ALL modes (survey, evaluate, propose, auto) — any time you need to find or read a paper.**

## Discover Papers

| Method | How | When |
|--------|-----|------|
| Semantic Scholar API | `curl -s "https://api.semanticscholar.org/graph/v1/paper/search?query=<KEYWORDS>&limit=20&fields=title,year,authors,citationCount,externalIds,abstract&sort=citationCount:desc"` | Keyword search |
| Semantic Scholar (recent) | Same but add `&year=2024-2026` | Cutting-edge work |
| Semantic Scholar (citations) | `.../paper/ArXiv:{ID}?fields=citations.title,citations.year,citations.authors,citations.externalIds,citations.citationCount` | Find successors |
| Web search | `WebSearch: "<topic>" site:arxiv.org` | Broad sweep |
| Papers With Code | `WebSearch: "<topic>" site:paperswithcode.com` | Benchmarks, code |
| Local DB | `python3 scripts/refs.py search "query"` | Already-collected papers |
| Fuzzy browse | `python3 scripts/search_refs.py "query"` | Interactive paper lookup |

## Read Papers

**ALWAYS try AlphaXiv first** for any arXiv paper — it provides structured markdown:

```
WebFetch: https://alphaxiv.org/overview/{PAPER_ID}.md    # structured overview (fast, try this first)
WebFetch: https://alphaxiv.org/abs/{PAPER_ID}.md         # full text (if overview lacks detail)
```

`{PAPER_ID}` is the arXiv ID, e.g., `2401.12345`. If AlphaXiv returns 404, fall back to the PDF.

**For key papers** (foundations, main competitors): use `/paper_related_works` logic to map predecessors and successors.

## Store Papers

**ALL discovered papers must go into refs.db immediately:**

```bash
python3 scripts/refs.py add --title "..." --authors "..." --year 2025 --arxiv "..." \
  --direction <current> --relevance high --notes "..." --relationship "..."
python3 scripts/refs.py update <id> --read --append-notes "Key insight: ..."
python3 scripts/refs.py link <version> <id> <role> --note "..."
```
